# Update mocks (same Figma file)

**Never spin a new file** for ongoing client project — extend existing file. Match existing polish.

**Before `use_figma`:** `figma-use` + `figma-generate-design`. Sequential `use_figma`.

## Inputs

**Existing file URL** (`fileKey`). Ask if missing. Clear change list.

## 1 — Audit (mandatory)

Inspect pages/names/counts. Collect **design DNA**: wrapper width; color/text/effect variables + styles; components (nav/footer/buttons/cards); spacing rhythm; naming patterns. Optional `use_figma` snippet to list pages if helpful.

Summarize DNA → **user confirms** before build.

## 2 — Plan

**New pages:** sections needed; map to existing patterns/components; realistic copy (no lorem); flag rare new components → approve first.

**Edits:** target node ids; text swap vs layout vs swap variants vs insert/remove section — minimize rebuild.

Present plan → approve.

## 3 — Build new pages

New page name matches conventions. Wrapper width/layout matches file. Section-by-section:

- Start from closest existing section pattern; reuse instances + variables
- Vary layouts (do not repeat same archetype >2×): media/text alternation, grids, quotes, stats, CTA band, icon grids, timeline, tables, FAQ, team/portfolio, etc.
- Imagery placeholders show intent/ratio
- Interactive states like library
- Mobile **375px** if other pages have mobile

After each section: screenshot — variables bound, styles applied, no clip, descriptive layer names.

## 4 — Modify existing pages

Locate nodes (`get_metadata` / read `use_figma`). Prefer edit auto-layout, `swapComponent`, text/style updates; insert/remove sections deliberately. Full-page screenshot after — check reflow around edit.

## 5 — Final check

Screenshot all touched pages; compare to untouched pages for consistency; page order sane; no orphaned junk frames.

Present screenshots + summary + open questions.

## New DS elements

Only if nothing fits — justify, **get approval**, mirror naming/structure, document on Foundations, bind to existing variables — no rogue hex.

## Anti-patterns

New file for update; off-palette fonts/colors; hardcode when variable/style exists; "lite" page vs rest of file; skip audit; rebuild untouched sections; default layer names; lorem; mobile skipped if file uses mobile; add DS pieces without approval.
